Description: Fragment of oval handle to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Astymedes. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0110.04. Probably same as Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 200, 18.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1070)
